---
title: Personal Cybersecurity 101
---

<% wrap_layout :blog_layout do %>

<div class="container">
  <h1>
    <%= current_page.data.title %>
  </h1>
  <ul>
    <li>Remove Flash
    <li>Remove Java
    <li>
      Set plugins as
      <%= link_to "'click-to-play'", "http://www.howtogeek.com/188059/how-to-enable-click-to-play-plugins-in-every-web-browser/", target: "_blank" %>
      in your browsers
    </li>
    <li>Use different password for each website <em>(see below)</em></li>
    <li>Use a password manager (so you can realistically do ^^). Or even write them down and store safely.</li>
    <li>Use two-factor authentication (2FA) wherever available</li>
    <li>Use the following browser extensions:
      <ul>
        <li><%= link_to "uBlock Origin", "https://github.com/gorhill/uBlock", target: "_blank" %></li>
        <li><%= link_to "HTTPS Everywhere", "https://www.eff.org/HTTPS-EVERYWHERE", target: "_blank" %></li>
        <li><%= link_to "Privacy Badger", "https://www.eff.org/privacybadger", target: "_blank" %></li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Use 'private mode' in your browser when appropriate</li>
    <li>Keep your stuff up to date - programs and operating system</li>
    <li>Use common sense</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<% end %>